        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 3:55PM MDT by NWS North Platte NE</headline>
        <description>At 355 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 24
miles south of Gordon, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Highway 61 crossing the Snake River, Big Hill, Morgan Lake, and
Billys Lake.

This includes Highway 61 between mile markers 194 and 200.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
